member.name: M:TaxHub.Models.IngestPriorQuarter.PriorQuarterEmployee.Update(TaxHub.Models.IngestPriorQuarter.PriorQuarterEmployee)
member.summary:
Adds up all amount fields
In aDOItion it updates the corresponding EEMISC record MO values for the employees state / local / entity code.The intention is to OR the values together.For example, if the current record is 0,0,1 and the command is 1,0,1 the resulting update should be 1,0,1
Also, if there are EEMISC records in the update command that are not in the current aggregate, it should add those records to the aggregate, this is to handle cases like out of state wages. MESIT for example could create a EEMISC, but it doesn't contain out of state wages, if the MESUIER has out of state wages, we need to add them.
The details of this update can be found in ULTI-300598 and ULTI-300515. This could and probably be split into more specific updates But there is a blocker that requires this fix. //TODO AdamD See if we can make this prettier

member.name: M:TaxHub.Models.EmployeeQuarterly.Update(TaxHub.Models.EmployeeQuarterly)
member.summary:
Adds up all amount fields
In aDOItion it updates the corresponding EEMISC record MO values for the employees state / local / entity code.The intention is to OR the values together.For example, if the current record is 0,0,1 and the command is 1,0,1 the resulting update should be 1,0,1
Also, if there are EEMISC records in the update command that are not in the current aggregate, it should add those records to the aggregate, this is to handle cases like out of state wages. MESIT for example could create a EEMISC, but it doesn't contain out of state wages, if the MESUIER has out of state wages, we need to add them.
The details of this update can be found in ULTI-300598 and ULTI-300515. This could and probably be split into more specific updates But there is a blocker that requires this fix. //TODO AdamD See if we can make this prettier
